o recognize these necessary underpinnings of any renewed nationalism, or the potentially troubling consequences that they would engender.To secure the general welfare in a new century, the future of American unity lies not in monolithic nationalism. Rather, Goldman suggests we move in the opposite direction: go small, embrace difference as the driving characteristic of American society, and support political projects grounded in local communities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCultural pluralismzUnited States. 0aNational characteristics, American. 0aNationalismzUnited States. 4aPolitical Science/Public Policy. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Ideologies / Conservatism & Liberalism.2bisacsh  aTrump.  ademocracy.  adifference.  aeuropean immigrant.  ahistory American conservatism.  alocalism.  anationalism.  aprotestantism protestant.  aright wing politics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021 Englishz978311075417908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021z9783110753943oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Pennsylvania Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073921340uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/978081229645740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780812296457423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780812296457/original  a978-3-11-073921-3  University of Pennsylvania Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075417-9  EBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_CL_SN